Q: In the figure shown, the ratio of $AB$ to $BC$ is $2:3$. What is the length of $AC$ if $AB$ is 18 units long? [asy]
size(5cm);

pair a = (0, 0); pair b = (18, 0); pair c = (36, 0);

draw(a--b--c--cycle);

label("$A$", a, S); label("$B$", b, S); label("$C$", c, S);
[/asy]

A: The answer is 36.
